
[1]scalp

   SCALP, n. [L. scalpo.]

   1. The skin of the top of the head; as a hairless scalp.

   2. The skin of the top of the head cut or torn off. A scalp among the
   Indians of America is a trophy of victory.

      SCALP, v.t. To deprive of the scalp, or integuments of the head.
